tionNode(ListNode headA, ListNode headB) {\\n        ListNode curr1 = headA;\\n        ListNode curr2 = headB;\\n        while(curr1 != curr2){\\n            curr1 = (curr1 == null)? headB : curr1.next;\\n            curr2 = (curr2 == null)? headA : curr2.next;\\n        }\\n        return curr1;\\n    }\\n}","compare_result":"11111111111111111111111111111111111111111","title_slug":"intersection-of-two-linked-lists","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1,"frontend_id":879},{"id":1951426454,"question_id":234,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"4\xc2\xa0days, 10\xc2\xa0hours","timestamp":1773771702,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"1318 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1951426454/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Palindrome Linked List","memory":"113.9 MB","code":"class Solution {\\n    public boolean isPalindrome(ListNode head) {\\n        String str = \\"\\";\\n        ListNode curr = head;\\n        \\n        // 1. Build the string from the Linked List\\n        while(curr != null) {\\n            str = str + curr.val;\\n            curr = curr.next;\\n        }\\n        \\n        // 2. Reverse the string\\n        String rev = new StringBuilder(str).reverse().toString();\\n        \\n        // 3. Compare and return\\n        return str.equals(rev);\\n    }\\n}","compare_result":"111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111","title_slug":"palindrome-linked-list","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1,"frontend_id":878},{"id":1950796166,"question_id":160,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"4\xc2\xa0days, 22\xc2\xa0hours","timestamp":1773728085,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"1 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1950796166/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Intersection of Two Linked Lists","memory":"52.6 MB","code":"/**\\n * Definition for singly-linked list.\\n * public class ListNode {\\n *     int val;\\n *     ListNode next;\\n *     ListNode(int x) {\\n *         val = x;\\n *